<paragraph id="16F3188EA9815D18D7C945F8A7F8591F" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F0C48399DF70A2DC30113ED6D5E94B52" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Deep water, 506 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3AFC472E4E0B91F24865E1C2D8C58576" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="58F18688F820D54F9FD4CD2F8AEE7F2C" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="826914E2E0071D806FFCDF791F2A9D1D" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">NE of Santa Cruz Island, Galapagos, East Pacific.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D672ADB4ACC5093AA3BA6795CD3BEE8D" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="172F0107135C8F3B2154184B1530C2CE" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="339AC0E5794FE6822D128B0EAE5EB37E" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
The species is assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="043A1CD2856329DDE94F5F65771B009A" class="Demospongiae" family="Calthropellidae" genus="Calthropella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calthropella (Pachataxa)" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Porifera" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pachataxa">Calthropella (Pachataxa)</taxonomicName>
on the basis of its spiculation. Size and shape of the calthrops is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DFCB585F938433C038FC43E1FA245B6B" class="Demospongiae" family="Calthropellidae" genus="Calthropella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calthropella (Pachataxa) lithistina" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="lithistina" subGenus="Pachataxa">Calthropella (Pachataxa) lithistina</taxonomicName>
, but these differ clearly in the diameter of the spheroxyasters (those of 
<taxonomicName id="ECDC69D140F06F81899775B45EB97D3D" class="Demospongiae" family="Calthropellidae" genus="Calthropella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calthropella (Pachataxa) pyrifera" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="pyrifera" subGenus="Pachataxa">Calthropella (Pachataxa) pyrifera</taxonomicName>
sp. n. are twice as large and these are also twice as large as those of 
<taxonomicName id="5561CDD885899CD8499683CED86A26F8" authority="de Laubenfels, 1936" authorityName="de Laubenfels" authorityYear="1936" class="Demospongiae" family="Calthropellidae" genus="Pachataxa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pachataxa enigmatica" order="Astrophorida" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="enigmatica">Pachataxa enigmatica</taxonomicName>
, see above). Especially the shape of the ataxasters renders this species distinct from the other two 
<taxonomicName id="C137FD610F5FC2BC10476299EBA3667C" class="Demospongiae" family="Calthropellidae" genus="Calthropella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calthropella (Pachataxa)" order="Tetractinellida" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Porifera" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Pachataxa">Calthropella (Pachataxa)</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
